30/12/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The health ministry announced on Thursday (29 December) that it has stepped up an immunisation campaign to contain a recent outbreak of measles.
Some 4,300 children have been infected and ten have died.
About 300,000 children have been immunised so far.
In other news, officials in Bucharest confirmed that a deadly variety of the avian flu has been detected in six villages east of the capital.
A British laboratory has determined the presence of the H5N1strain of the virus in dead poultry found in these areas.
(Reuters, AP - 29/12/05)
